      <h1 class='title'>Validity of maintenance agreements</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='grand-committee-report-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c290GC</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_290gc' title='Col. 290GC &mdash; HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c290GC' name='column_290gc' href='#column_290gc' rel='bookmark'>290GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03783'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_394' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        53 If a maintenance agreement includes a provision purporting to restrict any right to apply to a court for an order containing financial arrangements&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) that provision is void, but</li>
        <li>(b) any other financial arrangements contained in the agreement&#x2014;</li>
        <ol>
        <li>(i) are not void or unenforceable as a result, and</li>
        <li>(ii) unless void or unenforceable for any other reason, are (subject to paragraphs 54 and 58) binding on the parties to the agreement.</li></ol></ol>
      </p>
